FT  18 NOV 92 / World News In Brief: Convicted doctor allowed to practise
Consultant rheumatologist Dr Nigel Cox, 47, convicted of attempting to
murder a terminally ill patient at the Royal Hampshire County Hospital in
Winchester and sentenced to 12 months' imprisonment suspended for a year, is
to be allowed to continue to practise. The General Medical Council's
professional conduct committee ruled that his case should be concluded with
no further action.
